summary: An ordinance submitting to the qualified electors of the City of Seattle at the general municipal election to be held in said City on Tuesday, March 8, 1932, the proposition creating an indebtedness in the sum of $600,000.00 and the issuance and sale therefor of general negotiable interest bearing negotiable interest bearing serial coupon bonds of said City in said amount, for the purpose of paying a part of the cost of the improvement of Railroad Avenue from Madison Street to Bay Street by the constrution of a seawall and by filling, etc.
